    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flexible, sterile tubes that pass throught the urethra and into the bladder to drain urine. These feature two separate channels, one to drain liquid, and one to keep the catheter in place through the use of a balloon filled with sterile water. This type of catheter was developed by the urologist Frederic E.B. Foley in the 1930s.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
